The paper discusses a course on system design, which involves issues of systems engineering, structural models, and solving methods. These topics are closely related to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of optimization and multicriteria decision making, which are topics in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The laboratory works involve designing and implementing programs, which could fall under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the course is targeted towards developing skills in modular analysis and design of various multidisciplinary composite systems, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
